                    <comment id="12926705" author="thetaphi" created="Sun, 31 Oct 2010 13:29:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch that fixes XML parsing, to apply first move the hyphenation.dtd to the src/resource/ folder.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This patch also removed the hardcoded DTD from the parser and moves it to the resources folder (loaded by classloader). Solr is fixed to use the InputSource API, but it shozuld really use an URL, so ResourceLoader in Solr should be fixed to also supply URLs like ClassLoader!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="12926706" author="thetaphi" created="Sun, 31 Oct 2010 13:53:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Updated patch, uses Locale.ENGLISH as noted by Robert. Also leaves the DTD in place (Solr+Lucene tests, but it is never parsed, only if you would view the xml in the tests in your favourite XML reader)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
